    1.4. Insert xiaomi, apple, samsung to companies.

mysql> INSERT INTO phone_companies (id, name) VALUES (1, "Xiaomi"), (2, "Apple"), (3, "Samsung");
Query OK, 3 rows affected (0,01 sec)
Records: 3  Duplicates: 0  Warnings: 0

mysql> SELECT * FROM phone_companies;
+----+---------+
| id | name    |
+----+---------+
|  1 | Xiaomi  |
|  2 | Apple   |
|  3 | Samsung |
+----+---------+
3 rows in set (0,00 sec)

    1.5. Insert 3 phone (with any data) to phones.
    
mysql> INSERT INTO phones (phone_name, company_id, user_id) VALUES ("Xiaomi Redmi Note 9", 1, 1), ("Apple XR", 2, 2), ("Samsung Galaxy A32", 3, 3);
Query OK, 3 rows affected (0,03 sec)
Records: 3  Duplicates: 0  Warnings: 0

mysql> SELECT * FROM phones;
+----+---------------------+------------+---------+
| id | phone_name          | company_id | user_id |
